<br>
&quot;Oh , did anyone hear something about the US considering requesting UN or US troops to be sent to Palestine/Israel?&quot;<br>
<br>
They have been pushing this for years.  It isn't anything new.  The Palestinians don't want troops there that they may see as an Israeli ally.  Israel doesn't want troops there because they said they want to handle the situation themselves, and because they are constantly being told by outsiders to &quot;show restraint&quot; when they are attacked.  To make a long story short, neither side wants outside troop involvement because they don't feel that outsiders have their best interests at heart.  Outsiders are fine as mediators, but that is where both sides draw the line.  I think outside troops may help the situation, but that technically it isn't anyone else's business.  As much as I support Israel, I have to question whether it is right for Americans to be putting their lives on the line for another country.  If outside nations wanted an excuse to send troops to the region, then they had their chances in the past when the PLO started attacking people outside the Middle East that had nothing to do with the situation over there (ie. hijacking of Achilles Lauro, assasination of American ambassador, harboring of European terrorists, etc.), but that ship has sailed, and we currently don't have an excuse to be there.<br>
